snippet.textDisplay:
Could you imagine the UK if Josh V Fury happens? I'm 40..... there has been a lot of sporting events I remeber.
But Euro 96, man that was magical..... the party carnival feel in the air, it was second to none.
If they somehow arrange this fight in the UK in summer months, then shit the bed.
The country will be split, Joshua fans and Fury fans, it'll be a Friday day off work, build up parties, booze..... it would be shown here on Brighton beach on a massive screen, fucking beer tents, BBQ's..... both sets of fans mingling.
Then the fight..... and finally Sunday, everyone talking about the fight, knowing England and Brighton lol, people still boozing it up.
On the whole, it would be a unifying event, a masterclass event, and a fucking weekend to remember.
